==Useful Info==
'''Acid blobs''' are fast, [[acid]]ic monsters with highly accurate ranged and melee attacks that can [[corrode]] your armour and weapons. They deal enough damage that fragile characters should be more concerned about their [[HP]]. They can be found in [[the Slime Pits]].

{{monster spells}}

==Tips & Tricks==
*[[Resist corrosion]] reduces their damage output considerably and helps defend against the [[corrode]]d status.
*The Slime Pits aren't exactly easy to bottleneck enemies in, but if you can use [[wall]]s or other enemies to keep acid blobs from shooting you while you move into combat range, it'll help.
*Even with some form of acid resistance, these are still fast monsters that hit hard in melee: turn-for-turn, they have similar damage output to [[stone giant]]s. Prepare accordingly.
*They have terrible defenses. Low-accuracy spells such as [[Iron Shot]] are quite effective against them.
